 seems important to clean up unique database names to avoid clashes—maybe using UUIDs? I'm not sure if that needs to be deterministic, but I could use temporary names. It looks like I’ll need to manage the shutdown process and handle connections carefully to ensure everything closes as expected. I might need to assert that the context remains active during testing and consider unique in-memory databases for connection details.\n\n**Considering database configuration**\n\nI'm mulling over the DB_CLOSE_DELAY setting. Maybe setting it to -1 is fine for my purposes. I think I should also check if DB_CLOSE_DELAY=0 is an option. Hikari is the connection pool Spring uses, but I'm wondering if it’s included with boot-jdbc or if DataSourceBuilder chooses it when present. I need to figure out the right package for DataSourceAutoConfiguration in Spring Boot 4.1. It looks like it might be org.springframework.boot.jdbc.autoconfigure, but I'll inspect further.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0cf3cdaaa00a3958016a3eec7461088190a40d4ba2cf60e4f5\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPuyHio5cgu3nLQX7s3lmGYMrFTR4lJBXnPN9h-xK12KCUknMv_rH7zBNqrfmSFWSz25_2ffA9XhJNkljhN8BeeUxQbVzYbtqx_t-aidHslnLueRvOnl-nuoFt4iWHFJiub_iP1L2TtuVdkJ5xzpZ1kqP9XbAI_Q3Cj1EsCsoZSqvVAzjTyz8MT9lfrdVk5O_4PFeXXWASqYp3___SXyO7Tbl5STOKo5zdwKEDjSMpctAW6XwPwliCu8WcWfwF_03-_c2CrU9X9mhPc3NUvU_nponhR1clPlr_m8hdnL1TE0QYqqJSJjOZoeIx-8LGsI9H6m_o0BQmM-tg8RsY3HbtYfW83YJAVG2AkDbZnudTLN6QNPKeEX7vVNtnJty1NeacCwH2JuWUHhbcMTtzlEGSUkv0fq6D7mcYndxP-qAwrpYzCShCONkKo0U2BKmepdI2WWKrHa-3vtODEAiL-7Pxp2YryOuMbF9eJChsciT3YQtH6h-rrF3u46k1nK5h8YeXWV0dhh8rolAuOdZsKIZa7FDWpXa-TPOMZbdMjKR16Ye6028wW5mZ5-ZOh3uwMepr3CPSm0NiRAphexwYsrjLVxQzLaFFZ0rNlKKYVTbvV6off6D1Nb0X4WxlqgjsT0yONUX1FaAFBVy2j2p0O35ylnK1WSHH3PkSVb9R09fu2QzP7np-knt1BPThDh4j19JeghtA4FYM-E9e-fZX5J08wMbfbv_WbKh6BS-aDsF9bH21yu-KNKVrkcsQwv8UKcnB3uAwaG4TKPwAtqcb5VEB6AAxg6kvfqDe2LvFcEQH1cwc5sRd2XULIfHq0Aqa2WvaYMzMvrsn3etTENUk8TmqTYNLl4fuBkX6peVQliNI4myfWK