 changelog applies correctly. Using XML for changelogs might simplify things by avoiding additional dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Creating Temporary XML**\\n\\nI need to create a temporary XML file for the configuration setup. This will help manage my changelogs without running into dependency issues. It's essential that the XML structure is well-defined to work seamlessly with Liquibase. I’ll have to ensure that it's correctly formatted so that queries and data migrations can be handled efficiently. That way, I can bypass any potential risks associated with using YAML. Let’s get started on structuring this temporary XML file!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating database configuration**\\n\\nI'm testing auto-configuration conditions. It seems important to clean up unique database names to avoid clashes—maybe using UUIDs? I'm not sure if that needs to be deterministic, but I could use temporary names. It looks like I’ll need to manage the shutdown process and handle connections carefully to ensure everything closes as expected. I might need to assert that the context remains active during testing and consider unique in-memory databases for connection details.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering database configuration**\\n\\nI'm mulling over the DB_CLOSE_DELAY setting. Maybe setting it to -1 is fine for my purposes. I think I should also check if DB_CLOSE_DELAY=0 is an option. Hikari is the connection pool Spring uses, but I'm wondering if it’s included with boot-jdbc or if DataSourceBuilder chooses it when present. I need to figure out the right package for DataSourceAutoConfiguration in Spring Boot 4.1. It looks like it might be org.springframework.boot.jdbc.autoconfigure, but I'll inspect further.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_uvQMxT91e14H718n37YMgRxR|fc_0cf3cdaaa00a3958016a3eec87d4748190b2c0cda1a25c21c3", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap -classpath ~/.m2/repository/org/spring